CITATION FORMAT: All file-level citations across all pages use a standardized object shape:
  {file: '<repo-relative path>', lines: '<start-end>', confidence: <high|medium|low>}
Rules: (1) 'file' is repo-relative. Append ' [inferred]' if path is inferred; use '[not found]' if unlocatable. (2) 'lines' is inclusive 'start-end' range. Prefix '~' if uncertain beyond ±20 lines. Use null for whole-file references. (3) 'confidence' defaults to high. Use medium for ±10-20 line uncertainty; low for structural inference only. This object shape is reused identically in proficiency_evidence, evidence_units, and metrics — same schema everywhere enables uniform Stage 2 parsing.
